Example Solution

In your Index.cshtml where you define the popup editor for the grid:

@(Html.Kendo().Grid<VehicleModel>()
    .Name("vehicleGrid")
    .Editable(editable => editable.Mode(GridEditMode.PopUp))
    .Events(e => e.Edit("onVehicleEdit"))
    .DataSource(ds => ds.Ajax(/* your CRUD config */))
)


Now, in your script:

function onVehicleEdit(e) {
    // Locate the tabstrip inside the popup editor
    var tabStrip = e.container.find(".k-tabstrip").data("kendoTabStrip");

    if (tabStrip) {
        // Force reset to the first tab (index 0)
        tabStrip.select(0);
    }
}

Why this works

e.container is the popup editor container.

Inside it, youâ€™ve got a <div class="k-tabstrip"> (your Labour/SC/NSC/RB tabs).

.select(0) ensures the first tab is active every time the popup opens, regardless of what was open last.
